00290 /* DEFINTIONS for all the different types of nodes there are.  This is also used cross-referenced in utils.c so that I can get a string version 
00291  * of these names, so if you add new tpyes in here, be sure to add those same types in utils.c */

00293 {
00294         long unique_id;

00298 
00299         short traverse_visited; // a way to mark if we've visited yet
00300 
00301         npin_t **input_pins; // the input pins
00302         int num_input_pins;

00304         int num_input_port_sizes;
00305 
00306         npin_t **output_pins; // the output pins
00307         int num_output_pins;

00309         int num_output_port_sizes;
00310 
00311         short unique_node_data_id;
00312         void *node_data; // this is a point where you can add additional data for your optimization or technique
00313 
00314         int forward_level; // this is your logic level relative to PIs and FFs .. i.e farthest PI
00315         int backward_level; // this is your reverse logic level relative to POs and FFs .. i.e. farthest PO
00316         int sequential_level; // the associated sequential network that the node is in
00317         short sequential_terminator; // if this combinational node is a terminator for the sequential level (connects to flip-flop or Output pin
00318 
00319         netlist_t* internal_netlist; // this is a point of having a subgraph in a node
00320 
00321         short *associated_function;
00322 };
